Parkhurst boy
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a reformed juvenile offender sent from Parkhurst prison in the Isle of Wight to Auckland in the 1840s
Origin:British dialect
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also erroneously Parker's boy
